Fifty Wards Live 2019 Election Turnout Tracker

Welcome to the Fifty Wards turnout tracker! Voters across Chicago are sharing their turnout to support citizen science.

First, vote! Then, share your Division and Voter Number at http://bit.ly/chicagoturnout.

Live Results

As of 01:48, 500 voters in 50 wards have shared their voter number. I estimate that 1,077,233 people have voted across the city (95% Confidence Interval: 1,037,492 - 1,113,456).

Maps

I use historic correlations among precincts turnout to estimate turnout in the precincts with no data yet. I simultaneously estimate (1) the overall city-wide turnout, (2) precincts over-/under-performance, and (3) the city-wide time pattern of voting.
